3 Adding CSS to our document
To linkÂ styles.cssÂ toÂ index.html, add the following line somewhere inside theÂ &lt;head&gt;Â of the HTML document:
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" /&gt;
ThisÂ &lt;link&gt;Â element tells the browser that we have a stylesheet, using theÂ relÂ attribute, and the location of that stylesheet as the value of theÂ hrefÂ attribute. You can test that the CSS works by adding a rule toÂ styles.css. Using your code editor, add the following to your CSS file:
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" /&gt;
To target all paragraphs in the document, you would use the selector p.Â To turn all paragraphs green, you would use:
p {
  color: green;
}
You can target multiple selectors at the same time by separating the selectors with a comma. If you want all paragraphs and all list items to be green, your rule would look like this:
p,
li {
  color: green;
}

