    // custom query methods defined here
    Optional&lt;Book&gt; findBookByTitle(String title);
    Optional&lt;Book&gt; deleteBookByTitle(String title);
}
We use the @Autowired annotation to inject an instance of BookRepository into our Spring application, Springâ€™s dependency injection container will automatically instantiate a concrete implementation of the BookRepository interface and inject it into our applicationâ€™s bookRepository object.
This implementation is typically a proxy object that provides the required functionality for data access.
