1.2 What is â€œthisâ€
You may have noticed something slightly strange in our methods. Look at this one for example:


App.js

introduceSelf() {
  console.log(`Hi! I'm ${this.name[0]}.`);
}

You are probably wondering what this is. The this keyword refers to the current object the code is being written inside â€” so in this case this is equivalent to person. So why not just write person instead?
Well, when you only have to create a single object literal, itâ€™s not so useful. But if you create more than one, this enables you to use the same method definition for every object you create.

